                            <comment id="17248111" author="erans" created="Fri, 11 Dec 2020 18:42:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Unit tests added in commit a2c3868fb8115bccb2920d89388927ff889f619c (&quot;master&quot; branch).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;MatrixUtils.checkColumnIndex() uses COLUMN_INDEX instead of COLUMN_INDEX_OUT_OF_RANGE&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As it should be.&lt;br/&gt;
Instead of using many, many message templates, exceptions classes can use a feature (&lt;tt&gt;ExceptionContext&lt;/tt&gt;) that allows stacking of additional information about the failure.  The problem was in class &lt;tt&gt;OutOfRangeException&lt;/tt&gt; (see &lt;a href=&quot;https://gitbox.apache.org/repos/asf?p=commons-math.git;a=commit;h=323f6d71531599127e3b8edd5e13da2ea2c23c97&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;commit 323f6d71531599127e3b8edd5e13da2ea2c23c97&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the report, and the tests.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
